Frontend Cards (Phase 1)
1. Home Page (Places Near Me)
Get user location (GPS or manual input).
Show list of monasteries.
Filters: distance, type (Buddhist, Jain, etc.).
Each card: thumbnail, name, short details, distance.
2. Place Details Page
Show monastery details:
Name, description, founded year, history.
Thumbnail gallery.
Files available (3D model, audio guide, AR).
CTA: Open in 3D / AR Mode.
3. 3D View Page
Render monastery 3D model (file_path).
Controls: rotate, zoom, walk mode.
Info overlay: show guide info.
4. AR Interaction Page
Live camera feed.
Bot avatar overlay.
Bot speech: basic narration.
User mic → ask questions → bot responds.
5. Search / Explore Page
Dedicated search page (for users who don’t want GPS auto-detect).
Search by name, location, type.
6. Saved Monasteries / Favorites
User can save monasteries to revisit.
Show list of saved monasteries.

BAckend cards 
1. Monastery Listing (Nearby Places)
GET /api/monasteries?lat=xx&lng=yy&distance=km&type=buddhist
Response:
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Namgyal Monastery",
    "thumbnail": "/storage/thumbs/namgyal.jpg",
    "file_path": "/storage/models/namgyal.glb",
    "distance_km": 2.3,
    "type": "buddhist"
  }
]
2. Monastery Details
GET /api/monasteries/:id
Response:
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Namgyal Monastery",
  "description": "Founded in ...",
  "latitude": 32.2206,
  "longitude": 76.3202,
  "founded_year": 1564,
  "thumbnail": "/storage/thumbs/namgyal.jpg",
  "files": [
    { "type": "3d_model", "file_path": "/storage/models/namgyal.glb" },
    { "type": "audio_guide", "file_path": "/storage/guides/namgyal.mp3" }
  ]
}
3. 3D Model Fetch
GET /api/monasteries/:id/files?type=3d_model
4. AI Bot Query (for AR Mode)
POST /api/bot/query
Body:
{ "monastery_id": 1, "question": "When was this built?" }
Response:
{ "answer": "This monastery was founded in 1564 by ..." }
5. User Saved Monasteries
POST /api/user/saved
{
  "user_id": 123,
  "monastery_id": 1
}
GET /api/user/saved?user_id=123